cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.IT. 

The paper introduces a new model of one-way language acceptors, which is a variant of a checking stack automaton. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also investigates decidability properties of other variations of checking stack automata, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper discusses undecidability problems, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of reversal-bounded counters, which could suggest it belongs to cs.IT (Information Theory).
